    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but what is there to support? just more days of looking at his empty chair and feeling the cold? the doctors and the counselors... they don't understand. they don't live in this darkness. it feels more like a natural conclusion than a crisis. like a story that has simply reached its final, inevitable page. don't you see the poetry in it? the way everything beautiful eventually has to succumb to the dark?",
